cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper describes a computational implementation of the clonal selection principle for the adaptive immune response, which involves clustering and retrieval of immunological memory cells. This involves machine learning techniques such as affinity maturation and classification of medical data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image analysis (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.SI) techniques, which are less likely but still relevant to the research.
